celeste@coherent.com (Celeste C. Stokely) says that SunOS requires you
to use a separate name for each interface.  We have lots of
mulit-interface Suns.  We have a separate Internet address for each
but a single name.  We serve ND clients on all interfaces.  So there's
no specific SunOS requirement for separate names.  However it is true
that you do sometimes have to name a specific interface in a startup
file. I don't see that this is specific to SunOS.  We simply use the
actual address in such cases, though Mike Karel's suggestion of
assigning an additional name seems like a good one.

